Visualizations ¶

In [21]:
#Creating columns that will be important for visualizations
dataset['InvoiceDate']=pd.to_datetime(dataset['InvoiceDate'])
dataset['Year']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.year
dataset['Month']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.month
dataset['Month_name']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.month_name()
dataset['Week']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.strftime("%V")
dataset['Month_Year']=dataset['Month_name'] + '_' + dataset['Year'].astype(str)
dataset['Year_Month']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.to_period('M')
dataset['Hour']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.hour
dataset['Day']=dataset.InvoiceDate.dt.day
dataset['Date']=pd.to_datetime(dataset[['Year','Month','Day']])
dataset['Value'] = dataset['Quantity']*dataset['UnitPrice']

Monthly Analyses¶

In [27]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=1,figsize=(15,30))
rev = dataset[(dataset['Value']>0)&(dataset['Year']<=2011)]
rev = rev.groupby(rev['Year_Month']).agg({'Value':'sum',
                                          'Quantity': 'sum'
                                          })
rev = rev.reset_index()
rev = rev.rename({'Value':'Revenue'},axis=1)

#Plot 1: Revenue by Months
sns.set_style("darkgrid")
sns.barplot(data=rev, x=rev.Year_Month, y='Revenue', color='#1874CD', ax=ax[0])
ax[0].title.set_text('Revenue by Months')
plt.savefig('Revenuebymonths.png', bbox_inches= 'tight' )

#Plot 2: Quantity Sold by Months
sns.barplot(data=rev, x=rev.Year_Month, y='Quantity',  color='#1874CD', ax=ax[1])
ax[1].title.set_text('Quantity Sold by Months')
plt.savefig('quantitysoldbymonths.png', bbox_inches= 'tight' )

fig.suptitle('Monthly Analyses',fontsize=16,y=0.90)


plt.show()

Data Preparation ¶

The Data Preparation phase includes all of the tasks to prepare the dataset that are going to be applied in the next step. Some of the tasks are: outliers' removal, variables' scaling, missing values' imputation and feature engineering.

Outliers' Removal¶

In [28]:
# outlier filters
filters = ( 
    (dataset['UnitPrice'] > 0)
    &
    (dataset['Quantity'] > 0) 
    &
    (dataset['Quantity'] < 20000))

df = dataset[filters]

print('Percentage of data kept:', np.round(df.shape[0] / dataset.shape[0], 3))
